	"name": "Glutton for the Healing Arts",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/life/heart-broken-red.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 10th level, your body has become both accustomed to constant healing and more dependent upon it. You can sense healing spells, effects, and potions within 120 feet, whether you can see them or not.</p><p>If the you are the target of a healing spell, if you consume a healing potion, or if you are affected by a similar magical effect, you may receive half the healing (as per the healing roll) in order to gain a choice of 1 of the following effects for 1 minute:</p><ul><li><p>you gain a +1 bonus to your AC</p></li><li><p>you gain an expertise die on on Strength and Intelligence saving throws</p></li><li><p>gain 2 temporary points of exertion (which can be used just like any exertion points and can exceed your normal exertion pool)</p></li></ul><p>You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier (minimum of 1) per long rest.</p>",
